Review: Gagged, GAGGED the whole way through. He gaslit, gatekeeped, girlbossed his way to the most iconic and camp scene I HAVE EVER SEEN in recent years.
Duncan picking up Paul like a little kid always puts a smile on my face :)
GRIPPING my seat the whole time, phenomenal. I need more, Wes!! You can’t just leave me hanging like that… 🥲
I would’ve added an extra star for more stop motion. And here we are.
This one had more impact on me than it should’ve. I was in awe after the final shot, leaving me to wallow in my feelings.

Movie: The Wonderful Story of Henry Sugar
Review: The Wes Anderson-ism of it all fit Benedict and Dev extremely well. GOD I hope he incorporates them into the regular cast.
A heist with misogyny, sex, the French Judiciary system and Godard in his pyjamas at mental hospital. They might not seem connected, but I assure you they do.
Someone described this as a straight to vhs horror film that gets more unhinged as you go and I couldn’t agree more. I think I found a new one for group movie nights.

I appreciate what this doc is doing by ultimately showing, not telling and having us ultimately get the full history at the very end. Despite that, I didn’t need to know that much about how to cook an animal brain.
My family watches this every year as a coping mechanism after visiting relatives.

Movie: Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade
Review: What a better way to celebrate Jesus’ birthday with the thrilling search for the cup that people drank his blood out of!  Best Christmas ever! 🙂👍
Totally forgot to log this, but how did they animate this? Are these animators wizards or something????
